crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects Tiny Shell - an open-source UNIX backdoor
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Mandiant

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is a sophisticated backdoor that provides remote shell access and file transfer capabilities. It can operate in either a listen mode (server) or a connect-back mode (client), configured via command-line arguments (`-p` for port, `-c` for host). The backdoor uses a secret (`-s`) to authenticate and encrypt its command-and-control (C2) communications using a complex cryptographic algorithm. Its primary payload is a reverse shell, which it establishes by creating a pseudoterminal (`openpty`), redirecting standard I/O (`dup2`), and executing `/bin/sh` (`execl`).
